Package seng202.team5.accessor

Class AirlineAccessor

java.lang.Object
seng202.team5.accessor.AirlineAccessor
All Implemented Interfaces:
Accessor
public class AirlineAccessor
extends java.lang.Object
implements Accessor
AirlineAccessor Contains the functions save, update, delete, getData, and dataExists for airlines that directly interact with the database. Implements the Accessor interface.

    • update

      public int update​(int id, java.lang.String newName, java.lang.String newAlias, java.lang.String newIATA, java.lang.String newICAO, java.lang.String newCallsign, java.lang.String newCountry, java.lang.String newActive) throws java.sql.SQLException
      Updates a given airline with new data. Not every field must be updated.
      Parameters:
      id - The airline_id of the given airline you want to update.
      newName - The new name of the airline, may be null if not to be updated.
      newAlias - The new alias of the airline, may be null if not to be updated.
      newIATA - The new 2-letter IATA code of the airline, may be null if not to be updated.
      newICAO - The new 3-letter ICAO code of the airline, may be null if not to be updated.
      newCallsign - The new callsign of the airline, may be null if not to be updated.
      newCountry - The new country of the airline, may be null if not to be updated.
      newActive - The new active of the airline, "Y" or "N", may be null if not to be updated.
      Returns:
      int result The number of rows edited or -1 for error.
      Throws:
      java.sql.SQLException - Caused by ResultSet interactions.
